This paper is about computational semantic analysis, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) and falls under the category of computer science and artificial intelligence. The task proposed in the paper involves multi-way classification of semantic relations between pairs of nominals, which is a common problem in NLP. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). Other likely sub-categories include cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), as these sub-categories are also relevant to NLP and semantic analysis.
